.TH "devlink_port_register" 9 "devlink_port_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devlink_port_register \- Register devlink port
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" devlink_port_register
.BI "(struct devlink *devlink "  ","
.BI "struct devlink_port *devlink_port "  ","
.BI "unsigned int port_index "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "devlink" 12
devlink
.IP "devlink_port" 12
devlink port
.IP "port_index" 12
driver-specific numerical identifier of the port

Register devlink port with provided port index. User can use
any indexing, even hw-related one. devlink_port structure
is convenient to be embedded inside user driver private structure.
Note that the caller should take care of zeroing the devlink_port
structure.
